ww.rpgroup.caltech.edu/virus_bootcamp/assets/pdfs/339.1.full.pdf" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;rpgroup.caltech.edu/virus_boot&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;camp/assets/pdfs/339.1.full.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111051818080298498</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 10:57:47 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>PsychoPy</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@psychopy/111052298668961585</link><description>Coding an experiment from scratch can be a great way to learn python üêç If you'de like to get started we will be running a workshop on this next week! &lt;a href="https://workshops.psychopy.org/topics/coding-an-experiment.html#topicscode" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;workshops.psychopy.org/topics/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;coding-an-experiment.html#topicscode&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111052298668961585</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 13:00:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Jonathan Peelle</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@jpeelle/111047906422653682</link><description>For no reason in particular I made this highly accurate Venn diagram during a college meeting today&lt;a href="https://xkcd.com/773/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;xkcd.com/773/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/047/906/567/441/928/original/579a558866f0282f.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/047/906/567/441/928/original/579a558866f0282f.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111053459512918489</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 17:55:12 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Fediverse Report</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@fediversereport/111052178240781719</link><description>The Swiss Government has officially launched their Mastodon server at &lt;a href="https://social.admin.ch/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;social.admin.ch/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;In their official press release the Government confirms it is a trial for one year. They state that "Mastodon has several characteristics that make it fundamentally attractive for government communications", such as being beyond the control of others, as well as it being privacy friendly.Official press release: &lt;a href="https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-97696.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokument&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-97696.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Speaker of the Swiss Government: &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://social.admin.ch/@gov"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;gov&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111053815270063351</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 19:25:41 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>flypapers</title><link>https://botsin.space/@flypapers/111050705752644343</link><description>üì∞ "The spatial and temporal structure of neural activity across the fly brain" &lt;br/&gt; by üî¨ Evan S Schaffer, Neeli Mishra, Matthew R Whiteway, Wenze Li, Michelle B Vancura, Jason Freedman, Kripa B Patel, Venkatakaushik Voleti, Liam Paninski, Elizabeth M C Hillman, L F Abbott et al.&lt;br/&gt; &lt;a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37696814/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/376968&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;14/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://botsin.space/tags/Drosophila" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Drosophila&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://botsin.space/tags/Adult" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Adult&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111054043436662155</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 20:23:43 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111054578357169820</link><description>Oops.&lt;a href="https://pubpeer.com/publications/423064F786DE7F273604582DAE3149#" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;pubpeer.com/publications/42306&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;4F786DE7F273604582DAE3149#&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111054578357169820</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 22:39:45 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Cian O‚ÄôDonnell</title><link>https://mstdn.science/@cian/111053256823723564</link><description>In neurophysiology people often estimate "phase coherence", ie the trial-to-trial alignment of some brain signal (EEG/MEG/LFP) to some oscillation.This is hard using frequentist stats, so Sydney Dimmock, me &amp;amp; &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@conorjh" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;conorjh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  developed a better Bayesian method.Now in press in eLife: &lt;a href="https://elifesciences.org/articles/84602" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;elifesciences.org/articles/846&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;02&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111054871025966194</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 23:54:11 +0000</pubDate></item></channel></rss>